    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>General Operating System Description</title>
        <para>The BWB-Q100 Integrated Modular Avionics (IMA) Operating System provides a 
        partitioned execution environment compliant with ARINC 653 standards. This system 
        enables robust time and space partitioning for flight-critical applications.</para>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Key Features</title>
          <para>The operating system provides:</para>
          <para>- Time partitioning with deterministic scheduling</para>
          <para>- Space partitioning with memory protection units</para>
          <para>- Health monitoring and fault management</para>
          <para>- Inter-partition communication services</para>
          <para>- I/O management for AFDX and ARINC 429 interfaces</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Design Assurance Level</title>
          <para>The operating system kernel is developed to Design Assurance Level A (DAL-A) 
          in accordance with DO-178C standards for software considerations in airborne systems.</para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
